  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EU Scholarship Programme for the Turkish Cypriot community 2019-21</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EU Scholarship Programme for the Turkish Cypriot Community is being delivered by the British Council in Cyprus under a 43 month Delegation Agreement with the European Commission to implement the action for the calls for two academic years 2019/20 and 2020/21. The contract duration was extended to 55 months to manage the underspent which resulted from the withdrawal of scholars who could not start their studies because of Covid-19 pandemic. The value of the contract, however, remained the same. The EU Scholarship Programme is fully funded by the European Commission and forms part of one of four aid strands operated by the EU for the Turkish Cypriot Community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the Programme is to offer the Turkish Cypriot Community additional educational opportunities by raising their knowledge and/or increasing their skills in a specific field as well as broadening their experience of studying and working in the European Union, thus bringing them closer to the European Union.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Programme&apos;s target groups are final year high school students, graduates of high schools, final year undergraduate students, postgraduate students, University graduates and professionals from various sectors of the community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Programme included the following activities:                                                                             1) Launch &amp; promotion of the calls                                                                                                                2) Application &amp; recruitment process                                                                                            3) Selection process including the delivery of written tests                                                                                    4) Awards for successful applicants                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      5) Contract signing with beneficiaries                                                                                                                                                                                         6) Monitoring &amp; Evaluation                                                                                                                                                                                                    7) Alumni &amp; Visibility activities                                                                                                                                                                                                                   8) Final payment and closure of the Call</narrative>
  </description>
